<$fill $name="body">

!! Widget: `<$llm-chat>`

|!Attribute |!Description |!Default |
|`chatTiddler` |Tiddler to store conversation messages |required |
|`tiddler` |Source tiddler (sets `currentTiddler` for context) | |
|`systemPrompt` |System prompt text |global config |
|`tools` |Filter for tool tiddlers |none |
|`contextTemplate` |Context template tiddler title |precedence chain |

!! Widget: `<$llm-action>`

|!Attribute |!Description |!Default |
|`tiddler` |Source tiddler |none |
|`prompt` |Inline prompt text |none |
|`promptTemplate` |Prompt template tiddler title |none |
|`contextTemplate` |Context template override |precedence chain |
|`outputTarget` |Override template's output target |template value |
|`outputMode` |Override `text` / `markup` |template value |
|`tools` |Filter for tool tiddlers |none (no tools) |
|`systemPrompt` |Override system prompt |global config |

!! Context template fields

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/context-template`

|!Field |!Values |!Description |
|`template-name` |string |Display name |
|`template-description` |string |Description |
|`output-mode` |`text` / `markup` |How to render output |
|`output-target` |`display` / `field:<name>` / `new-tiddler` / filter |Where response goes |
|`inject-as` |`user-message` / `system-prompt` |How context is injected |
|`output-title-template` |string |Title pattern for new tiddlers (`$(currentTiddler)$` substitution) |
|`output-tags` |string |Tags for new tiddlers |
|`output-fields` |JSON |Additional fields for new tiddlers |

!! Prompt template fields

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/prompt`

|!Field |!Description |
|`prompt-name` |Display name |
|`prompt-template` |The prompt text |
|`context-template` |Default context template for this prompt |
|`output-mode` |Default output mode |
|`output-target` |Default output target |

!! Tool definition fields

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool`

|!Field |!Description |
|`tool-name` |Name sent to LLM (e.g. `search_tiddlers`) |
|`tool-description` |Description sent to LLM |
|`tool-schema` |JSON Schema for input parameters |
|`tool-mode` |`read` — render wikitext, return text output. `action` — render + invoke action widgets, return confirmation text (audit logged) |
|`tool-enabled` |`yes` (default) / `no` — disabled tools are excluded from LLM tool lists and cannot be invoked. Use this to keep work-in-progress tools inactive |

!! Per-chat tool selection

Each chat instance stores its active tools in the `llm-active-tools` field on its chat tiddler (a TiddlyWiki title list). Click the wrench icon in the chat header to open the tool selector:

* ''All / None'' — quick select/deselect all tools
* ''Group buttons'' — apply a tool group preset (replaces current selection)
* ''Checkboxes'' — toggle individual tools; hover for description

When `llm-active-tools` is not set, all built-in (shadow) tools are used by default. On first open, the selector initializes with built-in tools checked. The dropdown closes automatically when clicking outside it.

The orchestrator enforces tool selection at execution time — even if the LLM attempts to call a tool not in the active set, the call is rejected with an error message.

!! Tool groups

Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool-group`

|!Field |!Description |
|`group-name` |Display name shown in the tool selector |
|`group-description` |Tooltip text when hovering the group button |
|`group-tools` |TiddlyWiki title list of tool tiddler titles included in this group |

Groups are presets — clicking a group button in the tool selector replaces the chat's active tools with the group's tool set. Create and manage groups in Settings > Tool Groups.

A tool is considered ''complete'' when `tool-name`, `tool-schema`, and `text` (body) are all non-empty. Incomplete tools cannot be activated or cloned from the settings UI.

!! Built-in tools

|!Tool name |!Mode |!Description |
|`search_tiddlers` |`read` |Run a filter and return matching titles with tags |
|`get_tiddler` |`read` |Read a tiddler's fields and text |
|`set_field` |`action` |Set a field value on an existing tiddler |
|`create_tiddler` |`action` |Create a new tiddler with title, text, and optional tags |
|`delete_tiddler` |`action` |Delete a tiddler |
|`navigate_to_tiddler` |`action` |Open a tiddler in the story river so the user can see it |
|`wikitext_render` |`read` |Render wikitext and return the text output |

Action-mode tools (`set_field`, `create_tiddler`, `delete_tiddler`, `navigate_to_tiddler`) execute immediately and append an entry to the audit log at `$:/temp/rimir/llm-connect/write-log`.

!! Variables in tool wikitext

The property names from `tool-schema` become widget variables inside the tool's text body. For example, a schema with `"properties": {"title": ..., "filter": ...}` makes `<<title>>` and `<<filter>>` available.

|!Schema property type |!Variable value |
|`string` |The string as-is |
|`number` |String representation |
|`object` |JSON-serialized string |

Variables for parameters the LLM did not provide resolve to empty string.

!! Custom tools

Create custom tools from the Settings > Tools panel using ''Create new tool'' or ''Clone'' (copy icon on any existing tool). Clones start disabled (`tool-enabled: no`) so you can edit them before activation.

Alternatively, create a tool tiddler manually — tag it `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool` with the fields above. The tiddler body contains wikitext that receives LLM inputs as variables:

```
title: $:/my-tools/get-tagged
tags: $:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/tool
tool-name: get_tagged_tiddlers
tool-description: Get all tiddlers with a specific tag
tool-schema: {"type":"object","properties":{"tag":{"type":"string"}},"required":["tag"]}
tool-mode: read
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

<$list filter="[tag<tag>]" variable="item">
<$text text=<<item>>/>
</$list>
```

!! Bundled context templates

|!Template |!Tiddler |!Description |
|Pair editing |`$:/plugins/rimir/llm-connect/context-templates/pair-edit` |Sends the tiddler's raw wikitext for collaborative editing; output-mode `markup`, inject-as `user-message` |

!! Config tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Description |
|`$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/provider` |`claude` |Active provider |
|`$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/providers/<name>/api-key` | |API key |
|`$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/providers/<name>/model` |varies |Model ID |
|`$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/providers/<name>/max-tokens` |`4096` |Max response tokens |
|`$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/system-prompt` |default text |Global system prompt |
|`$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/confirm-writes` |`yes` |Currently unused — writes execute immediately with audit log |
|`$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/max-tool-result-length` |`4000` |Truncation limit |
|`$:/config/rimir/llm-connect/default-context-template` | |Global default template |

The `llm-active-tools` field on each chat tiddler controls per-chat tool selection. This is a TiddlyWiki title list managed by the tool selector UI — not a config tiddler.

</$fill>
</$transclude>
